commit.message:
Support 384kHz sample rates

Fixes #1298.
Cancel on lib error
Cleaner fallback handling, remove temporary file noise
fall back to previous config check if pkg_config doesn't work
use pkg_config to look up libfaad2 flags

Parse LAME header when mp3 was created with libavcodec

(Which as I understand it is just a wrapper for LAME.)

This is needed for gapless playback on these files.

Fix ignore_duplicates missing filtered tracks

Really just checking for duplicates again when unfiltering. A bit messy
but it does the job.

Relates to #423.
Fix player-next-album / player-prev-album with play_sorted

Fix gbuf to account for print width of control characters

Such characters are stored as one byte but print as "<07>" for example.
Remove unnecessary last variable in pl_delete_all
Fix alphabetical order of pl-delete in docs
Add error_msg to pl_delete_by_name
Do pl_create_default on pl_delete of last playlist
Move pl-delete-all to pl-delete -a
Add "pl-delete" command
Add "pl-delete-all" command
Add pl_delete_all function
Move playlist deletion code to new function

Allow cue plugin to parse cue sheet with multiple files.

The cue plugin will fail when parsing multiple FILE entry because of the
postion check and fixed file entry.

Make the parser more robust so it can paser the cue sheet with multiple
files.

Fix unmute when using softvol

Fixes #1278

Format whole number replaygain fields more naturally

In particular this avoids whole numbers printing with an extra "." at
the end.

Reduce R128 gain precision to 2 places of decimal

The encoding is only capable of accurately storing 2 decimal places.
It's misleading (and ugly) to present it as otherwise when printed.

[FFmpeg] Switch to new channel layout api

Old api is deprecated and sparks build warnings.

Add %{totaldiscs} to available format string

Allows displaying the number of discs of an album. Can also be used as a
condition.

Shorthand is `%T`.
mpris: use path basename for tracks with no title (#1281)

commit.message:
Add option to sort albums by name in tree view

By default they are still sorted by date, which is the current behavior.

I considered to also add an equivalent of smart_artist_sort, to strip
"The" from album names when sorting. It could be nice to add for
consistency, but I find it's not that useful when the list of albums
under a given artist tends to be quite small anyway.

Closes #909.
Implement option to ignore pasted text in normal mode (#1270)
Handle CSI escape sequences correctly

Add mouse bindings for right third of status bar

Default to play/volume.

Flag to prevent cycling with left-view / right-view

Added to the default mouse scroll binds, which is quite intuitive and
seems to be how web browsers like to handle it. (For reference they do
allow cycling when activated by keyboard shortcut, although we don't
have any default keyboard binds for left-view / right-view.)

Closes #1241.
